Sentencas: A Co3O4 enhanced La0.8Sr0.2Co0.5Fe0.5O3-delta (LSCF) electrode is developed for use in air electrodes with proton conducting solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC).
Titulo: Cobalt oxide enhanced lanthanum strontium cobalt ferrite electrode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The incipient wetness impregnation method enables Co3O4 nanoparticles on the LSCF surface without altering the bulk porosity of the LSCF electrode.
Titulo: Cobalt oxide enhanced lanthanum strontium cobalt ferrite electrode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The polarization resistance of LSCF electrodes is significantly reduced by Co3O4 doping, and both charge transfer and diffusion/conversion resistances were positively affected.
Titulo: Cobalt oxide enhanced lanthanum strontium cobalt ferrite electrode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The highest reduction in charge transfer resistance is obtained at 700 degrees C, which is increased from 21% to 32% through reduction of po(2).
Titulo: Cobalt oxide enhanced lanthanum strontium cobalt ferrite electrode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Conversely, the highest reduction in diffusion/conversion resistance is achieved at 550 degrees C. By increasing po(2), the reduction is increased from 57% to 66% and its activation energy is reduced up to 33% compared to pure LSCF.
Titulo: Cobalt oxide enhanced lanthanum strontium cobalt ferrite electrode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The lowest total area specific resistances obtained under air are 1.45 Omega.cm(2), 2.95 Omega.cm(2), 6.75 Omega.cm(2) and 16.45 Omega.cm(2) at 700 degrees C, 650 degrees C, 600 degrees C and 550 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: Cobalt oxide enhanced lanthanum strontium cobalt ferrite electrode for solid oxide fuel cells
